From: "Stephen A. Berger, M.D." <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

The following background data on dengue in Honduras were abstracted from the
GIDEON software program:
Dengue was first reported in Honduras in 1977. 112 492 cases were reported
in 1978 (including the country's first 5 cases of dengue hemorrhagic fever
or DHF -- all fatal).
Dengue is most common during August to November, among women and in the
North and Central areas of the country.
Year Cases -- DHF -- Fatal
1978 112 492 -- 5 -- 5
1979 1000
1980 2078
1981 1612
1982 1217
1983 719
1984 378
1985 307
1986 569
1987 261 *
1988 844
1989 2507
1990 1700
1991 5303 -- 16 -- 1
1992 2113 -- 1 -- 0
1993 2687
1994 4687
1995 28 064 -- 35 -- 5
1996 7564 -- NA -- 0
* 261 cases were officially reported in 1987; however, approximately 9500
cases were registered during an outbreak in Choluteca alone that year.
